<!-- FAQ -->
<section class="py-16 bg-green-50">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="text-center mb-12">
      <h2 class="font-heading text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900">Xeriscaping FAQ</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="space-y-4">
      <details class="group bg-white rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <summary class="flex items-center justify-between p-6 cursor-pointer">
          <span class="font-heading font-medium text-gray-900">What is xeriscaping?</span>
          <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-green-700 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">It's a landscaping approach designed for arid climates. Instead of fighting the desert with sprinklers and cool-season grass, you work with it — desert-adapted trees, flowering perennials, ornamental grasses, and targeted drip irrigation. A well-designed xeriscape has color, texture, and seasonal interest without the water bill or the Saturday morning mowing routine.</div>
      </details>
      <details class="group bg-white rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <summary class="flex items-center justify-between p-6 cursor-pointer">
          <span class="font-heading font-medium text-gray-900">What kind of water savings should I expect from xeriscaping?</span>
          <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-green-700 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">That depends on how much turf you're replacing and what your current irrigation setup looks like. In our experience across Las Cruces, homeowners typically see their outdoor water use drop somewhere between half and three-quarters after a full conversion. The savings compound — drip systems are inherently more efficient than spray heads, and desert-adapted plants simply need less water to begin with.</div>
      </details>
      <details class="group bg-white rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <summary class="flex items-center justify-between p-6 cursor-pointer">
          <span class="font-heading font-medium text-gray-900">Are there downsides to switching to xeriscape?</span>
          <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-green-700 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">Honestly, two things. First, the initial investment is higher than rolling out sod — you're paying for soil amendment, drip infrastructure, and mature plant material. The payback shows up on your water bill over the next few years. Second, design matters a lot. Without a solid plan, you end up with a gravel yard that nobody enjoys. That's why the plant selection and layout phase is worth spending time on.</div>
      </details>
      <details class="group bg-white rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <summary class="flex items-center justify-between p-6 cursor-pointer">
          <span class="font-heading font-medium text-gray-900">Will a xeriscape yard help or hurt my home value?</span>
          <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-green-700 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">In southern New Mexico, buyers are paying attention to water costs. A polished, fully planted xeriscape sends a clear message: this yard is low-maintenance, the irrigation is handled, and you won't be dumping money into a dying lawn every summer. Realtors we work with consistently tell us it helps listings stand out in the Las Cruces market.</div>
      </details>
      <details class="group bg-white rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <summary class="flex items-center justify-between p-6 cursor-pointer">
          <span class="font-heading font-medium text-gray-900">What's the typical timeline for a xeriscape project?</span>
          <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-green-700 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">A typical front-and-back conversion runs one to three weeks once we break ground. The first few days are demolition and soil work. Hardscape goes in next — usually two to four days depending on scope. Planting and drip line installation close it out. Before anything starts, you'll have a day-by-day schedule on paper.</div>
      </details>
      <details class="group bg-white rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <summary class="flex items-center justify-between p-6 cursor-pointer">
          <span class="font-heading font-medium text-gray-900">Where can I preview xeriscape plants before choosing?</span>
          <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-green-700 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">Absolutely. Las Cruces maintains a <a href="https://lascruces.gov/property/utilities/utility-services/water-conservation/" rel="noopener" target="_blank" class="text-green-700 hover:underline">water conservation demonstration garden on Motel Boulevard</a> where you can see mature examples of the desert willow, penstemon, agave, and other species we regularly install. It's free, open weekdays, and a great way to figure out what you like before we start designing.</div>
      </details>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

